U.S. territories, the life expectancy values given by the CIA World Factbook (included in the table above) and those of the [[Institute for Health Metrics and Evaluation]] (IHME) are not the same. The table below shows the 2017 / 2018 values given by both organizations for these territories.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Territory \n!United Nations (2018)!! Life expectancy, All<br> (in years),<br>CIA World Factbook<br> (2018)\n!World Bank 2017!! Life expectancy, All<br> (in years),<br> IHME (2017)\n|-\n|{{Flag|American Samoa}}\n| -||74.8\n| -||72.0\n|-\n|{{Flag|Guam}}\n|80.7||77.0\n|79.9||73.3\n|-\n|{{Flag|Northern Mariana Islands}}\n| -||76.1\n| -||76.4\n|-\n|{{Flag|Puerto Rico}}\n|80.7||81.3\n|79.8||78.2\n|-\n|{{Flag|U.S. Virgin Islands}}\n|81.2||79.8\n|79.6||74.4\n|}\n\n<small>Source: CIA World Factbook,<ref name=\"Factbook1\"/><ref name=\"Factbook2\"/><ref name=\"Factbook3\"/><ref name=\"Factbook4\"/><ref name=\"Factbook5\"/> Institute for Health Metrics and Evaluation at the University of Washington<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.healthdata.org/american-samoa|title=American Samoa|date=September 29, 2016|website=Institute for Health Metrics and Evaluation}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.healthdata.org/guam|title=Guam|date=September 29, 2016|website=Institute for Health Metrics and Evaluation}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.healthdata.org/northern-mariana-islands|title=Northern Mariana Islands|date=September 29, 2016|website=Institute for Health Metrics and Evaluation}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.healthdata.org/puerto-rico|title=Puerto Rico|date=September 29, 2016|website=Institute for Health Metrics and Evaluation}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.healthdata.org/virgin-islands-us|title=Virgin Islands, U.S.|date=September 29, 2016|website=Institute for Health Metrics and Evaluation}}</ref></small>\n==See also==\n{{sister project links|life expectancy}}\n*[[List of U.S. congressional districts by life expectancy]]\n*[[List of U.